🔹 Key Takeaways
1️⃣ Integrated Security is Essential

Modern threats span endpoint, identity, and cloud — protection must be coordinated, not isolated.

2️⃣ Detection to Response Must Be Unified

Signals from MDE and MDI gain value when correlated centrally in Sentinel with automation support.

3️⃣ Architecture Matters

Azure Landing Zones and RBAC ensure governance, scalability, and secure-by-design deployments.

4️⃣ Visibility + Automation = Faster Containment

Centralized monitoring and SOAR reduce detection time and accelerate remediation.



“To conclude, modern security cannot rely on standalone tools.

Threats today move across endpoints, identities, and cloud workloads — so protection must be integrated.

By combining endpoint detection, identity protection, centralized SIEM correlation, and automated response, we reduce detection time and improve containment speed.

At the same time, structured architecture through Landing Zones ensures governance and scalability from the beginning.

Overall, this approach delivers unified visibility, stronger security posture, and operational efficiency across the enterprise.”
